  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2019-12-19",
    "date": "2020-02-10T22:37:47Z",
    "text": "Parental Right to Know Act\n\nThis bill expands the scope of advance directive policies and related disclosures for providers under Medicaid and the Children's Health Insurance Program (CHIP).\n\nSpecifically, providers (e.g., hospitals, hospice programs, and home health care providers) must have advance directive policies for minors (rather than only adults). Providers must also disclose policies regarding parental access to a minor's medical records."
